data:
Activities of project “1st Place” will take place from 14 to 23 July, 2018, involving 36 participants from 7 countries - Latvia, Lithuania, Spain, Italy, Cyprus, Portugal and UK.
Nowadays, many youngsters choose to spend their free time sitting next to computers and phones and think less about their health and active participation in different processes. That’s way becomes project idea to promote an active and healthy lifestyle.
As we know, that healthy lifestyle is basis for great self-esteem and achievements in learning and sport. It provides a full body development and good looking, gives more energy and protects against diseases.
Aims of project are: 
-	to share experiences with good practice examples, how to promote a healthy lifestyle and understanding about it;
-	to give a chance to youngsters from different countries to meet, develop intercultural dialogue and be active, have opportunity to express themselves; 
-	to promote the popularity of healthy and active lifestyles among youth groups exposed to social exclusion and to improve the quality of life as a whole and to reduce social exclusion.
Result of project will be an active public event for project youngsters and  local community together, based on sports tournament, activities promoting an active and healthy lifestyle.
Project will increase the level of youngsters skills and abilities, including youngsters with fewer opportunities. It will also promote youth participation in democratic life in Europe and in labor market, intercultural dialogue, social inclusion and solidarity.
For project participants will be organized workshops with opportunity to reflect on their understanding and responsibility for the surrounding processes.
Project activities will be based on non-formal methods and basic principles: learning to be, learning to do, learning to be with others, and learning to learn. 
Realizing this project will have a positive effect on the local community by creating a wider understanding of the opportunities offered by EU
Through this project youngsters will have different effects: 
- develop the ability to design, plan, organize main event;
 - improve their self-assessment and analysis skills; 
- increase the skills and abilities to work with other young people in a team with different views; 
- creating new contacts; 
- improving communication skills through working groups and young people with fewer opportunities; 
- improving foreign language skills, the ability to learn new language; 
- improve your lifestyle.
